videos.description: Dalvin Warmack's 15-yard rushing touchdown puts Kansas State ahead 10-0.
videos.headline: Warmack takes it to the house for first Kansas State TD

videos.description: Tre King runs 25 yards to the end zone for the first Texas Tech touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: King makes big play to put Texas Tech on the board

videos.description: Alex Delton connects with Byron Pringle for a 19-yard touchdown pass to give Kansas State a 10-point lead.
videos.headline: Delton finds Pringle for another Kansas State TD

videos.description: Nic Shimonek finds KeKe Coutee for a 75-yard touchdown pass to close the gap to 17-14.
videos.headline: Shimonek delivers to Coutee for deep Texas Tech TD

videos.description: DT Kolin Hill is ejected for targeting after a late hit on Kansas State quarterback, Alex Delton in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Texas Tech's Hill ejected for targeting on late hit

videos.description: KeKe Coutee keeps his feet in bounds to score his second touchdown of the game and put Texas Tech ahead 21-17.
videos.headline: Coutee's TD gives Texas Tech their first lead

videos.description: Duke Shelley picks off Nic Shimonek's pass and takes it to the house for a 25-yard touchdown return and 24-21 lead.
videos.headline: Shelley gives Kansas State lead with pick-six

videos.description: Nic Shimonek connects with Dylan Cantrell for a 1-yard touchdown catch to put Texas Tech in front.
videos.headline: Shimonek finds an open Cantrell on 4th down for Texas Tech TD

videos.description: T.J. Vasher jumps and catches the football in the end zone to extend Texas Tech's lead 35-24 early in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Texas Tech's Vasher makes nice catch for TD

videos.description: Skylar Thompson gets to the end zone for a 1-yard touchdown. The Wildcats would get the two-point conversion to tie the game 35-35 with 42 seconds remaining in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Thompson punches it in for a Kansas State TD

videos.description: Skylar Thompson connects with Byron Pringle for a 8-yard touchdown pass to give the Wildcats a one-score lead in the first overtime.
videos.headline: Thompson fires to Pringle for Kansas State TD in OT
